From [FSH-6031|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/FSH-6031].
NPE in the deprecated EyeQL implementation when doing a search like {code}
https://crucible/api/rest/query?query=select%20revisions%20where%20csid%3D%27123%27%20return%20reviews&rep=MyRepo
{code}
if there is a review with a null description field.

This causes the JIRA-FishEye plugin to fail, as it currently uses that interface.

Perforce supports the "..." wildcard, comparable to the "**" antglob.
It matches zero or more path segments.
E.g.
{noformat}
$ p4 files //depot/.../images/...
//depot/Jamgraph/MAIN/images/jamgraph-jam.gif#1 - add change 768 (ubinary)
//depot/www/dev/images/jamgraph-jam.gif#1 - branch change 769 (ubinary)
//depot/www/review/images/jamgraph-jam.gif#1 - branch change 770 (ubinary)
{noformat}

FishEye is not able to handle them.
If I use {{//depot/.../images}} as depot path, FishEye slurps without errors but shows no files.

If the p4 binary is set to a location which does not exist, then FishEye will not start.
{noformat}
2011-06-13 21:58:12,663 ERROR [main] fisheye.app Run-mainImpl - Problem with config file: P4 executable does not exist at configured location: /opt/j2ee/domains/atlassian.com/eac-fisheye/fecru/fecru-2.7.0-M1-1466/sdfasfasfasf
